<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,158,1012]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,451,482,508]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Morphologic notes:—</emphasis>
This latter genus is characterized by its globose to cylindrical body of more than 
<quantity box="[1366,1422,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" unit="cm" value="4.0">4 cm</quantity>
in diameter, with tubercular or not ribs, with generally yellow bell-shaped flowers, less often pink or purple, with globular to cylindrical, woolly fruits. October and ends in February, depending on the species, getting right after.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,158,1012]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,876,590,617]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">
Notes on 
