<bibRefCitation author="Hunt, D. R. &amp; Taylor, N. P. &amp; Charles, G." box="[245,440,914,941]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" refId="ref8565" refString="Hunt, D. R., Taylor, N. P. &amp; Charles, G. (Eds.) (2006) The New Cactus Lexicon. Dh Books, Milborne Port, 373 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Hunt 
<emphasis box="[311,369,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
). According to the current recognition (
<bibRefCitation author="Anceschi, G. &amp; Magli, A." box="[895,1177,914,940]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" pagination="70 - 161" refId="ref7548" refString="Anceschi, G. &amp; Magli, A. (2018) A synopsis of the genus Parodia Spegazzini s. l. (Cactaceae) Bradleya 36: 70 - 161. https: // doi. org / 10.25223 / brad. n 36.2018. a 9" type="journal article" year="2018">Anceschi &amp; Magli 2018</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hofacker, A. &amp; Oliveira, A. S. &amp; Pontes, R. C." box="[1190,1439,914,941]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" pagination="341 - 345" refId="ref8476" refString="Hofacker, A., Oliveira, A. S. &amp; Pontes, R. C. (2020) Parodia roseolutea - eine bemerkenswerte Art aus Uruguay. Kakteen und andere Sukkulenten 71 (11): 341 - 345." type="journal article" year="2020">
Hofacker 
<emphasis box="[1304,1363,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">et al.</emphasis>
